input.stop_reason: The associated R7 SF Account is linked to a different Divvy SF Account ID than the triggered one.

block.comment: Stop job with error ... ERROR :: The associated R7 SF Account is linked to a different Divvy SF Account ID than the triggered one.
If the Divvy Account IDs do not match then we need to throw an error back to the triggered Divvy Account
If there is an existing DivvyLegacyID on the R7 Account we need to make sure the two Divvy Account ID fields match up
Else if the R7 SF Account does exist.. then we need to makes sure the associated R7 SF Account's Divvy Account field matches the triggered Divvy Account
Check to see if the associated R7 Account on the Divvy Account still exists in R7 .. if it doesn't send an error back to Divvy SF
Check to see if there is an existing R7 Account ID associated to the Divvy Account
See if there is already an R7 Account linked to the Divvy Account .. and if there is try to make sure the two accounts match up
